                    <br>
                    <i>
                        <a href="https://www.oyez.org/cases/2017/16-111">
                            Masterpiece Cakeshop, Ltd. v. Colorado Civil Rights Commission
                        </a>
                    </i>
                    (6/26/17)
                    <br>
                    Does the application of Colorado&#8217;s public accommodations law to compel a cake maker to design and make a cake that violates his sincerely held religious beliefs about same-sex marriage violate the Free Speech or Free Exercise Clauses of the First Amendment?
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    <i>
                        <a href="https://www.oyez.org/cases/2017/16-1436">
                            Trump v. International Refugee Assistance Project
                        </a>
                    </i>
                    (6/26/17)
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Are respondents&#8217; challenges to the temporary suspension of entry of aliens abroad under Section 2(c) of Executive Order No. 13,780 justiciable?</li>
                    <li>Does Section 2(c)&#8217;s temporary suspension of entry violate the Establishment Clause of the First Amendment?</li>
                    <li>Is the global injunction, which was the relief granted based on alleged injury to an individual plaintiff, impermissibly overbroad?</li>
                </ol>
                <br>
                <p>
                    <i>
                        <a href="https://www.oyez.org/cases/2017/16-1436https://www.oyez.org/cases/2017">
                            Christie v. National Collegiate Athletic Association
                        </a>
                    </i>
                    (6/27/17)
                    <br>
                    Does a federal statute that prohibits modification or repeal of state-law prohibitions on private conduct impermissibly commandeer the regulatory power of states in contravention of New York v. United States?
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    <i>
                        <a href="https://www.oyez.org/cases/2017/15-1439">
                            Cyan, Inc. v. Beaver City Employees’ Retirement Fund
                        </a>
                    </i>
                    (6/27/17)
                    <br>
                    Do state courts have subject matter jurisdiction over covered class actions that allege only Securities Act of 1933 claims?
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    <i>
                        <a href="https://www.oyez.org/cases/2017/16-1144">
                            Marinello v. United States
                        </a>
                    </i>
                    (6/27/17)
                    <br>
                    Does a conviction under 26 U.S.C. 7212(a) for corruptly endeavoring to obstruct or impede the due administration of the tax laws require that the government prove the defendant acted with knowledge of a pending Internal Revenue Service action?
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    <i>
                        <a href="https://www.oyez.org/cases/2017/16-492">
                            PEM Entities LLC v. Levin
                        </a>
                    </i>
                    (6/27/17)
                    <br>
                    Should bankruptcy courts apply a federal rule of decision (as five circuits have held) or a state law rule of decision (as two circuits have held) when deciding to recharacterize a debt claim in bankruptcy as a capital contribution?
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    <i>
                        <a href="https://www.oyez.org/cases/2017/16-534">
