            <p>
                <a href="https://www.oyez.org/cases/2016/16-1177">
                    <i>
                        Virginia v. LeBlanc
                    </i>
                </a> (6/12/17) <br/> The determination that Virginia’s geriatric release program satisfied <i>Graham v. Florida</i>’s requirement that juvenile non-homicide offenders be afforded a meaningful opportunity to obtain release was not an unreasonable application of the <i>Graham</i> rule. In a per curiam opinion, the Court held that, for a state court’s decision to be an unreasonable application of Supreme Court law, the decision must be so objectively unreasonable that there is no possibility for fairminded jurists to disagree.
