            <p>
                <a href="https://www.oyez.org/cases/2016/15-1194"><i>Packingham v. North Carolina</i></a> (6/19/17) <br/> The North Carolina law prohibiting registered sex offenders from accessing various websites, where minors are known to be active and have accounts, regardless of whether or not the sex offender directly interacted with a minor violates the First Amendment. Justice Anthony M. Kennedy delivered the opinion of the 5-3 majority.
            </p>
